FIGURE 7.

Eloeophila kintaro
(
Alexander, 1957
)

. 
A.
habitus, lateral view; 
B.
wing; 
C.
male terminalia, dorsal view; 
D.
outer gonostylus, ventral view; 
E.
aedeagal complex, dorsal view; 
F.
same, lateral view (left = dorsal); 
G.
paramere, dorsal surface. Scale bars: A–B, 2 mm; C–G, 0.1 mm.

subSubSection.paragraph:
Abdomen.
Brown to dark brown, caudal margin of each segment sometimes slightly dark. Male terminalia (
Figs 7C–G
) with outer gonostylus broad on basal half, bearing large pointed lobe at middle of outer margin; distal half narrow with small claw-shaped lobe at outer apical edge (
Fig. 7D
). Paramere with mesal-apical lobe flat fingershaped, about four times as long as wide and twice longer than lateral lobe (
Fig. 7G
). Aedeagus almost straight, about seven times as long as wide in lateral view (
Fig. 7F
). Apodeme of vesica directed anteroventrally (
Fig. 7F
).
